Finance Data Processing Backend

Overview This project is a backend application designed to manage
financial records efficiently with proper role-based access control. It
allows users to track transactions, view analytics, and manage data
securely through REST APIs.

Tech Stack - Node.js - Express.js - MongoDB (Mongoose) - JWT (JSON Web
Tokens)

Project Structure src/ controllers/ models/ routes/ middleware/
services/ utils/ app.js

Authentication The application uses JWT-based authentication. Once a
user logs in, a token is generated which must be included in requests to
access protected routes.

Roles & Permissions Viewer - Can only view records Analyst - Can view
records and dashboard insights Admin - Full control (create, update,
delete records)

Features

User Management - User registration and login - Role-based access
control - Manage active/inactive users

Financial Records - Add, update, delete transactions - Filter by type,
category, and date - Pagination support

Dashboard APIs - Total income and expenses - Net balance - Category-wise
analysis - Monthly trends - Recent transactions

API Endpoints

Auth POST /api/auth/register POST /api/auth/login

Records POST /api/records GET /api/records PATCH /api/records/:id DELETE
/api/records/:id

Dashboard GET /api/dashboard/summary GET /api/dashboard/categories GET
/api/dashboard/trends GET /api/dashboard/recent

Setup Instructions 1. Clone repository 2. Run: npm install 3. Create
.env file and add: PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/financeDB JWT_SECRET=your_secret 4.
Run: npm run dev

Assumptions - Roles are predefined (viewer, analyst, admin) - Only admin
can modify records - Basic validation implemented

Additional Features - JWT authentication - Filtering and pagination -
Aggregation APIs

Future Improvements - Add unit tests - Add refresh tokens - Improve
validation - Add frontend dashboard
